rulesync supports a permissions.json canonical format for tool permissions.

FORMAT:
{
  "permission": {
    "bash": { "*": "ask", "git *": "allow", "rm *": "deny" },
    "edit": { "*": "deny", "src/**": "allow" }
  }
}

Actions: allow, ask, deny. Maps tool categories to glob patterns.

CURRENT STATE: Only Claude Code appears to consume this (maps to allowedTools/permissions in settings). No other providers have native permission systems.

PRIORITY: Low. Niche feature, single-provider consumption. But could become more relevant as providers add permission systems. Worth tracking.
